<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="773" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d773">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/10245</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Director of the Bureau of Enemy Trade, War Trade
                                    Board</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">McGonigal</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-13">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 13, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your inquiry of June 1,
                                    1918,<note n="1" xml:id="d773fn1">Not printed.</note> the
                                Department begs to inform you that for purposes of the dispatch of
                                postal correspondence and the remittance of funds, Roumania should
                                be regarded, for the present, as territory occupied by the enemy.
                                For your information, I may add that there is no consular office of
                                the United States in Roumania at present.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>